Download python here and install it:
https://www.python.org/downloads/

Set the python interpreter as your environment variable:
To ensure smooth operation of these scripts and tools, you might want to consider adding this directory to your system's PATH. Here's how you can do it:

Right-click on the Start button and select System.
Click on Advanced system settings on the right side.
In the System Properties window, go to the Advanced tab.
Click on the Environment Variables button near the bottom.
Under the System variables section, find and select the Path variable.
Click on the Edit button.
In the Edit Environment Variable window, click on the New button and paste your path EXAMPLE: C:\Users\daryl\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python311\  and C:\Users\daryl\AppData\Local\Programs\Python\Python311\Scripts
Click on OK to close each window.

Download and install CUDA:
https://developer.nvidia.com/cuda-downloads?target_os=Windows&target_arch=x86_64&target_version=11&target_type=exe_local

install pytorch here:
https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/

EXAMPLE:
pip3 install torch torchvision torchaudio --index-url https://download.pytorch.org/whl/cu117

Validate install here:
https://pytorch.org/get-started/locally/#windows-verification

python --version

pip list


